snippet.textDisplay: the way Linus uses the cooler, its actually impossible to cool the phone. From the backside the CPU is on the right side, and from the front (screen side) the CPU is on the left. On the backside of the phone there is some plastic (nylon) protecting the motherboard. Only viable option is to try cooling the phone from the screen side. The s10 actually has a vapor champer between the motherboard and chassi, the vapor chamber is on the screen side. The screen has pretty good heat transfer (it has a graphene film).

snippet.textDisplay: At the height of Pokemon Go I would just carry around reusable hand warmers.  They were about the size of playing cards and could be frozen like what is commonly used in lunch boxes.  Would keep the phone cool for about 30-45 minutes before I noticed thermal throttling, then could swap out another one.  There were nearly small enough to fit into the case and could just toss them back into the freezer each night.
